-- BOE's Sentance Says `Gradual' Rate Increase in U.K. Would Help Recovery
-- Anchalee Worrachate
-- 2010-07-17T11:35:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/boe-s-sentance-says-gradual-rate-increase-in-u-k-would-help-recovery.html

          
          
             (Corrects typographical error in second paragraph.)  
 A “gradual” increase in U.K.
interest rates “would be helpful for the recovery,” Bank of
England policy maker  Andrew Sentance  told the British
Broadcasting Corp.  
 Sentance spoke in an interview broadcast today on BBC Radio
4’s Money Box program.  
